	<section name="title" styleuri="/xusr/share/doc/styles_1060/style_title.xsl">
		<content>
			<name>Sink crud_document</name>
			<text>Accessor to update a document in the named database</text>
		</content>
	</section>
	
	<section name="definition" styleuri="/xusr/share/doc/styles_1060/style_definition.xsl">
		<content>
			<module>urn:com:mindalliance:channels:crud</module>
			<format>
				<sub name="format"/>
			</format>
			<returns>
				<b>t</b>
			</returns>
			<syntax>
				<type><b>copy</b></type>
				<operand req="true">this:param</operand>
        <database req="true">databse name</database>
				<target req="true">active:crud_document</target>
			</syntax>
		</content>
		<includes>
			<include name="format" type="xml">
		    <instr>
		      <type>copy</type>
		      <operand>
            <project>
              <id>878AD470F6C983655BEE25411</id>
              <name>My project</name>
            </project>
		      </operand>
          <database>data:dbName</database>
		      <target>active:crud_document</target>
		    </instr>
			</include>
		</includes>
	</section>
	
	<section name="purpose" styleuri="/xusr/share/doc/styles_1060/style_basic.xsl">
		<content>
	    <p>
				Updating is done by sinking an xml document into the <code>crud_document</code> accessor. 
        It deletes the document  (the prior version), if any, with the same id as the updated document (the new version)
        and then the updated document is stored in the currently opened model.
			</p>
			<p>If successful the response is a boolean indicating whether a prior version was removed, otherwise an exception is thrown.</p>
		</content>
		<includes/>
	</section>
</document>